        <p class="aboutMeText">Hi, My name is Tylar Knox and I'm apart of the 2021 high school graduating class!
            I was born in Chicago, Illinois and raised in Boston, Massachusetts where I began to develop a passion
            in creativity which I've expressed through art. At a young age I enjoyed making things out of cardboard as well
            as painting and drawing. As I got older I discovered a new way to express my passion for creating things which is through
            computer programming and web development.</p>

        <p class="aboutMeText">Throughout my high school career at Madison Park Technical Vocational High School I've
            studied computer programming and web development and fell in love with it. I've been able to create multiple
            websites as well as computer programs such as animations, games, and calculators. I've been able to learn about different
            coding languages, a few of them being JavaScript, HTML/CSS and Python.</p>

        <p>Apart from the technical side of computer programming I've learned how to work towards a goal until I
            reach it. If the way I'm doing something isn't working out it's always possible to find another
            solution. I've also gotten familiar with how to utilize my resources. Sometimes it's necessary to look
            something up on the internet or communicate with someone and ask them questions so you can better
            understand what you're doing.</p>
